OL,3,CEvidence suggests link between
OL,4,C'forever chemicals' and some health
OL,5,Cconditions
OL,7,FJersey government has shared new
OL,8,Ffindings from a report that's
OL,9,Fattributed a long-lasting chemical
OL,10,Fcalled PFAS as a possible cause of
OL,11,Fcertain types of cancer and other
OL,12,Fconditions.
OL,14,FHowever, the data remains inconclusive
OL,15,Fdespite some insisting that it has
OL,16,Fcontributed to life-changing illnesses.
